<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - ROCKER ARM ASSEMBLY, CAMSHAFT, TAPPETS AND PUSH RODS -
        CAMSHAFT, TAPPETS &#38; PUSH RODS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CAMSHAFT, TAPPETS &#38; PUSH RODS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="bold">Refer to the appropriate manual sections for removal instructions for fuel,
                    turbocharger, cylinder head and front cover items.
                </emph>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove roller tappets and roller tappet guides from their bores. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050517">5.17</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Mark the tappets as to location in the crankcase, so they can be returned to their
                            original position.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050518">5.18</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . for location of gears and timing marks.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the fuel injection pump timing gear as outlined in Section 11
                    <hotlnk document="e105_E10511.xml" xrefid="e10511">"FUEL INJECTION PUMP"</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the engine so that timing marks on lower and upper idler gears, crankshaft and
                    camshaft gear are aligned.
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050517" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2336" filename="../figeg2/EG2336.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.17.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Roller Tappets</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Roller Tappet Guide</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050518" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2345" filename="../figeg2/EG2345.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.18.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Rear Half, Front Cover</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Injection Pump Gear Timing Marks</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Upper Idler Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Upper Idler/Lower Idler Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. Lower Idler Gear Timing Marks</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. Lower Idler Gear/Crankshaft</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. Crankshaft</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. Pressure Regulator Valve (80 psi)</callout1>
                        <callout1>9. Camshaft Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1>10. Camshaft</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>PRIOR TO REMOVING ANY GEAR, MOUNT A MAGNETIC BASE DIAL INDICATOR ONTO THE ENGINE AND CHECK
                            FOR GEAR BACKLASH AND END PLAY. REFER TO SECTION 8, "TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER" FOR
                            INSTRUCTIONS.
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove idler gears as described in Section 8
                    <hotlnk document="e105_E10508.xml" xrefid="e10508">"TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER"</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>When the engine is mounted in a turn-over stand, rotate engine so front of engine is
                            facing up (engine in vertical position). This position allows for easy removal of camshaft
                            assembly.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the camshaft gear so the access holes in the gear align with the thrust plate
                    retaining bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two thrust plate bolts and washers. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050519">5.19</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the camshaft from the crankcase by lifting the assembly straight up. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050520">5.20</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>This method reduces the risk of damaging the camshaft journals and/or bushings.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef1050519" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2352" filename="../figeg2/EG2352.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.19.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Camshaft Gear</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Access Hole/Bolt</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050520" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2353" filename="../figeg2/EG2353.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 5.20.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Camshaft Assembly</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Crankcase</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
